       Third International Conference on
       Human Centered Processes HCP-2007

              (sponsored by EGC)

       Vilnius, Lithuania, May 15-18, 2007

          http://www.mii.lt/HCP-2007


This third conference is in the line of the series of Human Centered
Processes conferences held previously at Brest (France, 1999) and in
Luxembourg (2003). However, it will behave a plenary conference, 
workshops, tutorials, poster sessions and a doctoral colloquium.

Topics of Interest (non exhaustive list): Cognitive approach to decision 
making, Multi-agent paradigm in distributed decision making, Knowledge 
discovery and data visualization, Human abilities/skills in man-machine 
interaction, Cognitive engineering and design, Action/decision systems 
in E and M-commerce, Context management in human centered processes, 
Intelligent decision support for sustainable development, Modeling of 
political-social processes, Intelligent computer teaching systems, 
Case-based supervised cross learning, Language engineering, Speech 
recognition, Ethical dilemmas in decision making, Software 
internationalization and localization, Ontologies and conceptualization, 
etc.

HCP 2007 is sponsored by EGC and we invite EGC members to propose papers and workshops dedicated to human factors in data mining and knowledge managment.

Some important Dates

 Conference submissions and workshop proposals due  :  15 November 2006
 Workshops acceptance                               :  01 December 2006

Conferences Chairs
 Gilles Coppin, Chair of the Steering Committee
 Patrick Brézillon, Chair of the Programme Committee
 Leonidas Sakalauskas, Chair of the Organizing Committee

 HCP 2007 web site for information and contact: http://www.mii.lt/HCP-2007






